community and dream new social possibilities. Bebop’s complexity and radicality, Leal contends, made it possible for those like Araki, Salinas, and Wing who grappled daily with state-sanctioned violence to challenge a racially supremacist, imperial nation, all while hearing and making the world anew.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aBop (Music)xHistory and criticism2DLC. 0aBop (Music)xHistory and criticism. 0aJazzxHistory and criticism2DLC. 0aJazzxHistory and criticism. 0aJazzxSocial aspectsxHistoryy20th centuryzUnited States. 0aJazzxSocial aspectszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century2DLC. 0aJazzxSocial aspectszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aJazzzJapanxHistory and criticism2DLC. 0aJazzzJapanxHistory and criticism. 0aMusic and racezUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century2DLC. 0aMusic and racezUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Jazz.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311099775008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023 Englishz978311131909408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023z978311131812740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478024583?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478024583423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478024583/original  a978-3-11-099775-0  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131812-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131909-4  EBOOK P